member.name: T:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType
member.summary: Vehicle propagators (available for vehicle types listed in parentheses).

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType.eUnknownPropagator
member.summary: Unknown propagator (all vehicles).

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType.ePropagatorHPOP
member.summary: High Precision Orbit Propagator (satellites and missiles): handles circular, elliptical, parabolic and hyperbolic orbits at distances ranging from the surface of the Earth to the orbit of the Moon and beyond.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType.ePropagatorJ2Perturbation
member.summary: J2 Perturbation (1st-order) (satellites): accounts for secular variations in the orbit elements due to Earth oblateness, but does not model atmospheric drag or solar or lunar gravitational forces.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType.ePropagatorJ4Perturbation
member.summary: J4 Perburbation (2nd order) (satellites): accounts for secular variations in orbit elements due to Earth oblateness, but doesn't model atmos. drag or solar or lunar grav. forces. Includes 1st and 2nd order effects of J2 and 1st order effects of J4.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType.ePropagatorLOP
member.summary: Long-term Orbit Propagator (satellites): allows accurate prediction of the motion of a satellite's orbit over many months or years.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType.ePropagatorSGP4
member.summary: SGP4 (satellites): a standard AFSPACECOM propagator used with two-line mean element (TLE) sets.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType.ePropagatorSPICE
member.summary: SPICE (satellites): reads ephemeris from binary files that are in a standard format produced by the Jet Propulsion Laboratory (JPL).

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType.ePropagatorStkExternal
member.summary: STK external (all vehicles): allows you to read the ephemeris for a satellite from a file.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType.ePropagatorTwoBody
member.summary: Two Body(Keplerian motion) propagator (satellites and missiles): considers only the force of gravity from the Earth, which is modeled as a point mass.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType.ePropagatorUserExternal
member.summary: User-External propagator.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType.ePropagatorGreatArc
member.summary: Great Arc (aircraft, ships and ground vehicles): defines a point-by-point path over the surface of the Earth with position and altitude defined at each point.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType.ePropagatorBallistic
member.summary: Ballistic (missiles): defines vehicles following an elliptical path that begins and ends at the Earth's surface.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType.ePropagatorSimpleAscent
member.summary: Simple Ascent (launch vehicles): creates an ascent trajectory based on launch and insertion parameters.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType.ePropagatorAstrogator
member.summary: Astrogator propagator.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType.ePropagatorRealtime
member.summary: Realtime propagator.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType.ePropagatorGPS
member.summary: GPS propagator

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType.ePropagatorMissionModeler
member.summary: Aircraft Mission Modeler propagator

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType.ePropagator11Param
member.summary: The 11-Parameter propagator models geostationary satellites using 11-Parameter files. The propagator uses an algorithm documented in Intelsat Earth Station Standards (IESS) IESS-412 (Rev. 2), available at www.celestrak.com.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEVePropagatorType.ePropagatorSP3
member.summary: The SP3 propagator reads .sp3 files of type 'a' and 'c' and allows you to use multiple files in sequence. These files are used to provide precise GPS orbits from the National Geodetic Survey (NGS).

member.summary: Class defining Central Body Obstruction constraints.

remarks.para: Note on Solar/Lunar Obstructions
Please note the following regarding the relationship between setting Solar/Lunar in the GUI and in this Object Model:

If you select the Solar/Lunar Obstruction checkbox on the Sun Constraints page, it sets both the Sun and the Moon as obstructions. If you then want to remove one or both of these obstructions in the Object Model, you must use the RemoveObstruction method twice, i.e., once for each body.
Similarly, to set the Sun and the Moon as obstructions in the Object Model, you must use the AddObstruction method twice.

remarks.para: Note on Solar/Lunar Obstructions
Please note the following regarding the relationship between setting Solar/Lunar in the GUI and in this Object Model:

If you select the Solar/Lunar Obstruction checkbox on the Sun Constraints page, it sets both the Sun and the Moon as obstructions. If you then want to remove one or both of these obstructions in the Object Model, you must use the RemoveObstruction method twice, i.e., once for each body.
Similarly, to set the Sun and the Moon as obstructions in the Object Model, you must use the AddObstruction method twice.

member.summary: The minimum step size that is allowed to be taken.

member.summary: Specifies the fixed step size for the fixed step control.

member.summary: Controls alignment of samples with a UTC time grid. Using proper time bound can improve computational performance if the ephemeris lies on a fixed UTC time grid. The time bound determines the reference time for taking fixed step samples.

member.name: T:AGI.STKObjects.AgEAtmosphericDensityModel
member.summary: Atmospheric density models.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEAtmosphericDensityModel.e1976StandardAtmosModel
member.summary: 1976 Standard Atmosphere: look-up model based on the satellite's altitude, with a valid range of 86km - 1000 km.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEAtmosphericDensityModel.eCira72
member.summary: CIRA 1972: empirical model of atmospheric temperature and densities as recommended by the Committee on Space Research (COSPAR).

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEAtmosphericDensityModel.eExponentialModel
member.summary: Exponential Model: uses equation calculating atmospheric density on basis of a specified altitude, reference density, reference altitude and scale altitude.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEAtmosphericDensityModel.eHarrisPriester
member.summary: Harris-Priester: takes into account a 10.7 cm solar flux level and diurnal bulge. Uses density tables. Valid range of 0-1000 km.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEAtmosphericDensityModel.eJacchiaRoberts
member.summary: Jacchia-Roberts: similar to Jacchia 1971 (below) but uses analytical methods to improve performance.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEAtmosphericDensityModel.eJacchia60
member.summary: Jacchia 1960: outdated atmospheric model provided for making comparisons with other software.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEAtmosphericDensityModel.eJacchia70
member.summary: Jacchia 1970: computes atmospheric density based on the composition of the atmosphere, which depends on altitude as well as seasonal variation. Valid range is 100-2500 km.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEAtmosphericDensityModel.eJacchia71
member.summary: Jacchia 1971: similar to Jacchia 1970 (above), with improved treatment of certain solar effects.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEAtmosphericDensityModel.eMSIS00
member.summary: NRLMSISE 2000: finds the total density by accounting for the contribution of N, N2, O, O2, He, Ar and H. Includes anomalous oxygen. 2000 version, valid range of 0-1000 km.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEAtmosphericDensityModel.eMSIS86
member.summary: MSIS 1986: finds the total density by accounting for the contribution of N2, O, O2, He, Ar and H. 1986 version, valid range of 90-1000 km.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEAtmosphericDensityModel.eMSIS90
member.summary: MSISE 1990: finds the total density by accounting for the contribution of N2, O, O2, He, Ar and H. 1990 version, valid range of 0-1000 km.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEAttCoordinateAxes.eAttCoordinateAxesInertial
member.summary: Each central body defines its own Inertial frame computed as a constant rotation from the ICRF frame. Earth and Sun both define their Inertial frames as ICRF itself (i.e., no rotation) and do not provide an additional frame named Inertial.

member.name: T:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod
member.summary: Dilution of Precision method.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eGDOP
member.summary: Geometric Dilution of Precision: Measures the dilution of precision for the entire navigation solution.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eHDOP
member.summary: Horizontal Dilution of Precision: Measures the dilution of precision for the horizontal (latitude/longitude) components of the positional portion of the navigation solution.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eHDOP3
member.summary: Same as HDOP, but the DOP value is computed even if only 3 navigation sources are available, in which case the clock component is ignored.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.ePDOP
member.summary: Position Dilution of Precision: Measures only the dilution of precision associated with the positional portion of the navigation solution.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.ePDOP3
member.summary: Same as PDOP, but the DOP value is computed even if only 3 navigation sources are available, in which case the clock component is ignored.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eTDOP
member.summary: Time Dilution of Precision: Measures the dilution of precision of the time portion of the navigation solution.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eVDOP
member.summary: Vertical Dilution of Precision: Measures the dilution of precision for the vertical (altitude) components of the positional portion of the navigation solution.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eVDOP3
member.summary: Same as VDOP, but the DOP value is computed even if only 3 navigation sources are available, in which case the clock component is ignored.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eGACC
member.summary: Geometric Accuracy: Measures the accuracy of the entire navigation solution.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eHACC
member.summary: Horizontal Accuracy: Measures the accuracy for the horizontal (latitude/longitude) components of the positional portion of the navigation solution.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eHACC3
member.summary: Same as HACC, but the DOP value is computed even if only 3 navigation sources are available, in which case the clock component is ignored.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.ePACC
member.summary: Position Accuracy: Measures only the accuracy associated with the positional portion of the navigation solution.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.ePACC3
member.summary: Same as PACC, but the DOP value is computed even if only 3 navigation sources are available, in which case the clock component is ignored.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eTACC
member.summary: Time Accuracy: Measures the accuracy of the time portion of the navigation solution.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eVACC
member.summary: Vertical Accuracy: Measures the accuracy for the vertical (altitude) components of the positional portion of the navigation solution.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eVACC3
member.summary: Same as VACC, but the DOP value is computed even if only 3 navigation sources are available, in which case the clock component is ignored.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eEDOP
member.summary: East Dilution of Precision: Measures the dilution of precision for the east components of the positional portion of the navigation solution.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eEDOP3
member.summary: Same as eEDOP, but the DOP value is computed even if only 3 navigation sources are available, in which case the clock component is ignored.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eNDOP
member.summary: North Dilution of Precision: Measures the dilution of precision for the east components of the positional portion of the navigation solution.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eNDOP3
member.summary: Same as eNDOP, but the DOP value is computed even if only 3 navigation sources are available, in which case the clock component is ignored.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eEACC
member.summary: East Accuracy: Measures the accuracy for the east components of the positional portion of the navigation solution.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eEACC3
member.summary: Same as EACC, but the DOP value is computed even if only 3 navigation sources are available, in which case the clock component is ignored.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eNACC
member.summary: North Accuracy: Measures the accuracy for the north components of the positional portion of the navigation solution.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgEFmMethod.eNACC3

member.summary: Reserved for look ahead propagators that are not currently supported

member.summary: The HoldCBIPosition look ahead propagator keeps position and velocity constant in the inertial (i.e., CBI) frame.

member.summary: The HoldCBFPosition look ahead propagator keeps position and velocity constant in the fixed (i.e., CBF) frame.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgELookAheadPropagator.eLookAheadTwoBody
member.summary: Two-Body is an analytical propagator that generates ephemeris by evaluating a formula.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgELookAheadPropagator.eLookAheadJ2Perturbation
member.summary: The J2 Perturbation (first-order) propagator accounts for secular variations in the orbit elements due to Earth oblateness.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgELookAheadPropagator.eLookAheadJ4Perturbation
member.summary: The J4 Perturbation (second-order) propagator accounts for secular variations in the orbit elements due to Earth oblateness.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgELookAheadPropagator.eLookAheadDeadReckon
member.summary: The DeadReckon look ahead propagator projects the motion of the vehicle along a straight line, along the last velocity vector.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.AgELookAheadPropagator.eLookAheadBallistic
member.summary: The Ballistic Propagator defines an elliptical path that begins and ends at the Earth's surface. Specifying a fixed flight time, initial velocity or altitude can further refine the shape of the trajectory.

member.summary: Origin is at the center of the Earth and axes which are fixed to the Earth.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects._IAgVeRealtimePointBuilder.LLAHPS
member.summary: Lat & Lon are entered in Lat & Lon units. Alt is in Distance unit. Heading & Pitch are in degrees. Speed is in Distance/Time. Heading is entered as degrees from North and is the rotation about the Z-axis; Pitch is the rotation about the Y-axis.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects._IAgVeRealtimePointBuilder.LLA
member.summary: The LLA measures <Alt> from the surface of the Earth, or 0.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects._IAgVeRealtimePointBuilder.AGL_LLA
member.summary: The AGL_LLA considers terrain at the specified location when measuring <Alt>.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects._IAgVeRealtimePointBuilder.MSL_LLA
member.summary: The MSL_LLA considers mean sea level at the specified location when measuring <Alt>.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects._IAgVeRealtimePointBuilder.UTM
member.summary: Valid values for ZoneStr are A, B, Y, Z or ddc, where 00<dd<61 and c is C-X. Easting, Northing and Alt are entered in distance units. LonRate and LatRate are entered in degrees/second. AltRate is entered in units/second.

member.summary: Returns the type of the solar radiation pressure model

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.AgSRPModelGPS.Scale
member.summary: Multiplicative factor on top of nominal GPS solar pressure model for acceleration in the satellite body fixed X-Z plane, which contains the sun to satellite line. Also known as K1, the nominal value is near 1.0.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.AgSRPModelGPS.YBias
member.summary: Acceleration along the body-fixed Y axis of the satellite. Input is unitless but is multiplied by 1.0e-12 m/s2 to yield an acceleration perpendicular to the sun-to-satellite line. Also known as K2, the nominally value is in the range of -1 < YBias < 1.

member.name: T:AGI.STKObjects.AgVePropagatorSP3
member.summary: The SP3 propagator reads .sp3 files of type 'a' and 'c' and allows you to use multiple files in sequence. These files are used to provide precise GPS orbits from the National Geodetic Survey (NGS).

member.name: M:AGI.STKObjects.AgVePropagatorSP3.Propagate
member.summary: Propagates the vehicle's path using the specified time interval

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.AgVePropagatorSP3.InterpolationOrder
member.summary: An interpolation order of 1 specifies linear interpolation and is appropriate for closely spaced data or data with significant jitter. Higher interpolation orders yield more accurate interpolation when the data is smooth and continuous.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.AgVePropagatorSP3.InterpolationMethod
member.summary: By default, the SP3 propagator uses the standard Lagrange interpolation scheme, interpolating position and velocity separately. Some files may be configured to allow the Hermitian interpolation.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.AgVePropagatorSP3.InterpolateAcrossBoundaries
member.summary: Whether to interpolate across file boundaries. If this option is set, STK will interpolate ephemeris steps according to the user-defined Step Size between the end of one SP3 file and the beginning of the next.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.AgVePropagatorSP3.Extrapolate1PastEnd
member.summary: Extrapolate 1 step beyond last data point. If this option is selected, STK will calculate an additional ephemeris step beyond the last data point provided by the SP3 file(s) assigned to the satellite.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.AgVePropagatorSP3.SatelliteIdentifier
member.summary: A selected satellite identifier.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.AgVePropagatorSP3.Files
member.summary: Access and manipulate the collection of SP3 files. You can add multiple files to a single satellite object and - if there are no gaps between the files - the whole ephemeris will be propagated in sequence.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.AgVePropagatorSP3.AvailableIdentifiers
member.summary: An array of available satellite identifiers.
